@ENDNODE

@NODE WHAT_IS_FBASE
@TITLE "What is FBase?"

   FBase stands for Floppy Base and is a simple database used to hold
   information about the contents of floppy disks.

   The programs enables you to read the entire directory tree of a disk,
   edit the data, and then use the @{"Find" link DO_FIND} command to search
   for specific files. You may also print your database contents for hard-
   copy refrence.

@ENDNODE

@NODE GENERAL_CONCEPTS
@TITLE "General Concepts"

   Data in FBase is stored by Floppies. Each Floppy entry holds the complete
   directory tree for that disk. This tree is made of Records. each Record
   holds data about one file or directory.

   Record data can be further edited in the @{"Contents Window" link FLOPPY_CONTENTS}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE INSTALLING
@TITLE "Installing FBase"

   Copy FBase and FBase.info to any directory. If you wish to use the on-line
   help copy also FBase.guide to that directory.

   Run the program wither from the WorkBench or from CLI/Shell.

@ENDNODE

@NODE REQUIREMENTS
@TITLE "FBase Requirements"

   To use FBase you need KS2.04+ and the incredible @{"MUI" link MUI} (Magik User Interface)
   package version 1.4+.

   Due to MUI large overhead it is best to run the program on machines with
   1MB of memory or more.
   The program incurs some memory overhead (about 40 bytes per Record) but
   there should be no problem in holding a massive amount of data in memory.

@ENDNODE

